    "0.1 ' ' 1 1) results based on cluster-robust inference (var-cov estimator: CR2, approx t-test and confidence interval, df: Satterthwaite approx)",
    "ent example that may require a more complex approach to model dependency in effect size data is when multiple instruments are used across studies to assess a certain outcome, in addition to primary studies reporting on multiple effect sizes (Fern ˊandez-Castilla et al., 2019).",
    "In this scenario, effect sizes are nested within studies, but at the same time effect sizes are assessed with a specific instrument that may have been used across studies.",
    "The type of instrument now serves as a \"crossed random effect\" that is sometimes referred to as a \"cross-classified random effect\".",
    "In this cross-classified model, effect sizes can vary because of sampling variability, within-study variability, and both between-study and between-instrument variability."
  ],
